notes_display: Medal commemorates bounties from country’s expanding colonies.
issue_obverse_figure_description_s: George II, cuirass, sash, star of Order of the Garter, perruque, laurel crown.
issue_obverse_legend_s: GEORGIUS II . D . G . MAG . BR . FR . ET HIB . REX .
issue_reverse_figure_description_s: Britannia, seated on seashore, holds olive branch and and a staff with the Liberty cap; her lion reposes at her feet.  At left, Mercury, representing Commerce, empties a cornucopia.  At right, an infant genius measures a globe.  Two ships head out to sea.
issue_reverse_legend_s: HÆ TIBI SUNT ARTES ("these are thy arts")
